Checklist for College Students: Responsible Use of Social Media

Do's 
1.) Before you post, think.
2.) Use Strong Passwords and Make Appropriate Adjustments to Privacy Settings To Secure Your Privacy.
3.) Check the news before sharing it.
4.) Always be respectful in comments and discussions, even if you disagree. 
5.)Use Pinterest for inspiration, LinkedIn for networking, and YouTube for learning.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Must-Nots.
1.)Give out your private details like phone number, address, password.
2.)Engage in cyberbullying, trolling, or online feuds.
3.)Post anything that might harm your reputation.
4.)Trust or spread news unless verified and facts.
5.)Spend too much time on social media which has a bad effect on your studies and health.
